<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250636>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Calyptotheca lardil n. sp. A – C, holotype (MTQ G 26483). A, general view of autozooids, and ovicellate zooids, with a kenozooid at right centre; B, autozooid; C, primary orifice with suboral avicularium—note the oval distal opesia; D – E, paratype (MTQ G 26485). D, ancestrula; E, whole colony with ancestrula." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250636/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

